This paper focuses on RDF query optimization, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that utilizes graph matching and join-based query implementation, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the correlations among operations, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
